supportive for acute hepatitis b. interferon-alpha and reverse transcriptase inhibitors for chronic hepatitis b. treatment response, particularly interferon treatment, differs by hbv genotype. treatment is expensive and often not available in developing countries. in southeast asia, medicinal herbs are widely used to treat chronic hbv disease, of which the efficacy is yet unclear. liver transplant is possible for decompensated cirrhosis.
