early detection and containment of human-to-human p. knowlesi transmission in the event of a complete emergence into the human population; vector control; antimosquito measures.
mosquitoes, principally canopy-dwelling haemagogus and sabethes spp. the virus has also been isolated from psorophora, mansonia and culex spp.
